text: Taylor Terrell (July 22, 1991 – July 21, 2016) was an American news anchor for 41NBC News at Daybreak and 41Today at WMGT-TV in Macon, Georgia. Terrell died on the eve of her 25th birthday after slipping over Rainbow Falls, a waterfall in North Carolina. == References == == External links == * Profile at 41NBC Category:2016 deaths Category:1991 births Category:African-American women journalists Category:African-American journalists Category:Journalists from Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Television anchors from Atlanta Category:Georgia Southern University alumni Category:Accidental deaths from falls Category:American women television journalists
